<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 02 at 11:23PM CDT until May 03 at 12:00AM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN RANDALL AND SOUTHERN POTTER COUNTIES...
At 1123 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Amarillo,
moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Amarillo and Mescalero Park.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
